CSS Layout

Lets see an example of Website Layout. It is divided into headers, menus, content and a footer.

1. HEADER - A header is usually located at the top of the website (or right below a top navigation menu). 
            It often contains a logo or the website name:
                          For Example - .header {
                                         background-color: #F1F1F1;
                                         text-align: center;
                                         padding: 10px;
                                       }
                                       
2. NAV Bar - A navigation bar contains a list of links to help the visitors navigating through your website:

Let's see an example - /* The navbar container */
                       .topnav {
                             overflow: hidden;
                             background-color: #333;
                         }

                      /* Navbar links */
                        .topnav a {
                        float: left;
                        display: block;
                        color: #f2f2f2;
                        text-align: center;
                        padding: 14px 16px;
                        text-decoration: none;
                      }

                     /* Links - change color on hover */
                      .topnav a:hover {
                       background-color: #ddd;
                       color: black;
                    }
                    
3. CONTENT - It basically depends on the target users of how the layout in this section is used and depicted.
             The most common layout is one (or combining them) of the following:-
                       1-column (often used for mobile browsers)
                       2-column (often used for tablets and laptops)
                       3-column layout (only used for desktops)
                       
       Let's see an example of 3-column Layout -
              /* Create three equal columns that float next to each other */
                     .column {
                     float: left;
                     width: 33.33%;
                   }

              /* Clear floats after the columns */
                    .row:after {
                     content: "";
                     display: table;
                     clear: both;
                   }

              /* Responsive layout - makes the three columns stack on top of each other instead of next to each other on smaller screens (600px wide or less) */
                    @media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
                    .column {
                    width: 100%;
                   }
               }
               
 4. FOOTER - The footer is placed at the bottom of your page. 
             It often contains information like copyright and contact info:
                For example - 
                      .footer {
                           background-color: #F1F1F1;
                           text-align: center;
                           padding: 10px;
                       }
